tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE ProteinStructures (
    protein_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    protein_name VARCHAR(255),
    structure_file BYTEA,
    interaction_partner_id UUID
)

CREATE TABLE ProteinStructures (
  protein_id INT,
  protein_name VARCHAR(255),
  structure TEXT,
  PRIMARY KEY (protein_id)
)

CREATE TABLE ProteinInteractions (
  interaction_id INT,
  protein_id_1 INT,
  protein_id_2 INT,
  interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
  PRIMARY KEY (interaction_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (protein_id_1) REFERENCES ProteinStructures(protein_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (protein_id_2) REFERENCES ProteinStructures(protein_id)
)

CREATE TABLE ProteinFunctions (
  protein_id INT,
  function_name VARCHAR(100),
  description TEXT,
  PRIMARY KEY (protein_id)
)

CREATE TABLE ProteinMutations (
  mutation_id INT,
  protein_id INT,
  mutation_type VARCHAR(50),
  mutation_description TEXT,
  PRIMARY KEY (mutation_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (protein_id) REFERENCES ProteinStructures(protein_id)
)

CREATE TABLE ProteinLocalization (
  localization_id INT,
  protein_id INT,
  localization_type VARCHAR(50),
  localization_description TEXT,
  PRIMARY KEY (localization_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (protein_id) REFERENCES ProteinStructures(protein_id)
)
